<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\c_bloom\c4101_philethis</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>50</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>A creature floats before you, hidden inside its voluminous cloak, unmoving and unmoved by your presence. It observes the slave market with a scholar's avid disinterest.

Exactly who, or what, the thing is - man or machine, mutant or monster - is impossible to discern. Its glass face reveals nothing but your reflection; its mechanical voice reveals nothing at all. 

You recall that this creature is known as a philethis, but you don't know anything else about them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've seen you before, haven't I?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The hall was dark, and the plasmar gleamed. Together, we posed questions."

That seems the only answer it intends to give.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>This philethis seems remarkably similar to the one you met in Sagus Cliffs. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis turns from the slave market and, through some subtlety of posture, conveys a willingness to entertain further conversation.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>Abruptly its glass face twists in your direction. In a rasping, uninflected voice, it asks, "Why did the child wail?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you trying to find?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Farewell."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Courage."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And so it goes."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That is the way it is."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>Indeed, it is *identical* to the other one in every respect.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>If it notices your presence, it gives no sign. Instead, it watches the slave market with a scholar's avid disinterest.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What child are you talking about? A slave?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's just what children do - they cry."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps it was frightened."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have no time for pointless questioning."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps it was hurt."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps it was angry."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>For a span, the philethis stands still and silent. Then, with a gasp like the opening of an old vault, it sighs. "Ahh."

After a moment, it seems to nod slightly, as if inviting you to pose questions of your own.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Without a further sound, the philethis turns back to the slave market.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>Your own voice echoes back at you from within the folds of the philethis's robes. "I have no time for pointless questioning." The creature gives no further acknowledgment.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I have no time for pointless questioning."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps it was wronged."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>From the philethis comes the shrill whine of mechanical parts or inhuman vocalization. Eventually, the sound changes to a word. "Irrelevant."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps it was lonely."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do you know anything about the Bloom?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me more about the Bloom."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A socket, a doorknob, a crumbling cliff - these are not your face. Each that is, is itself." The words, already slow, screech to a stop. Its glassy face cocks slightly, and a whirr comes from within its robes. 

"The mirror does not look back. The Bloom cannot teach, but it leaves scraps. One gathers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis silently contemplates the question for a time, then answers simply, "No."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>In a strange, piping voice, the philethis replies, "A mudlark on the bank of the river Time."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>A long, low exhalation comes from the philethis. "The question."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm looking for someone - a fellow castoff of the Changing God."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis leans its huge bulk toward you such that your face swells and deforms in its round reflection.

"You yourself must find." The thing's voice grates with labored certainty.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Is there something I can do to help you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I said, can I help you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>The question hangs before the silent philethis. It gives no answer; not even one of the varied sounds of its contemplation. 

Eventually, it becomes clear that nothing will come.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>Again, the philethis stands silent.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you approach the philethis, it gives an immense groan, like some vast hulk breaking at sea. At last, the groan becomes a word. "Violator!" 

A moment later, in a blinding flash of light, it vanishes.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do you know where I can find a Maw?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You will."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
